===Noun===
'''prang'''
#(UK slang)  A car [[crash]] without any casualties, typically minor; as in (US) [[fender-bender]]. (Believed to have originated in the [[RAF]] during WW2).
#Meaning to get paranoid about something (be in a state of paranoia).
#(US slang) Synonym for crack cocaine.

===Verb===
'''to prang'''
#to [[crash]], to have an [[accident]]